main event: A reddish-white object was observed moving slowly in a zigzag course over San Diego, California on April 6, 1950.
interesting points: The object was observed for 15 seconds and disappeared to the north., It moved at low altitude, unlike typical meteors or aircraft., The witness considered the possibility of it being a reflection or a meteor, but it did not fit these categories., The report includes two sketches of unidentified flying objects, one cigar-shaped and the other cloud-like., The investigation was closed due to lack of witnesses or physical evidence.
witness description: All interested people described in the attached report, no specific witnesses were confirmed.
